hedt:Pavor-nocturnus a hed:HedTag ;
    rdfs:label "Pavor-nocturnus" ;
    rdfs:comment "A nocturnal episode characterized by age of onset of less than five years (mean age 18 months, with peak prevalence at five to seven years), appearance of signs of panic two hours after falling asleep with crying, screams, a fearful expression, inability to recognize other people including parents (for a duration of 5-15 minutes), amnesia upon awakening. Pavor nocturnus occurs in patients almost every night for months or years (but the frequency is highly variable and may be as low as once a month) and is likely to disappear spontaneously at the age of six to eight years." ;
    heda:inLibrary "score" ;
    heda:suggestedTag hedt:Clinical-EEG-temporal-relationship,
        hedt:Episode-awareness,
        hedt:Episode-consciousness,
        hedt:Episode-event-count,
        hedt:Episode-phase,
