hedt:Six-Hz-spike-slow-wave a hed:HedTag ;
    rdfs:label "Six-Hz-spike-slow-wave" ;
    rdfs:comment "Spike and slow wave complexes at 4-7Hz, but mostly at 6 Hz occurring generally in brief bursts bilaterally and synchronously, symmetrically or asymmetrically, and either confined to or of larger amplitude over the posterior or anterior regions of the head. The spike has a strong positive component. Amplitude varies but is generally smaller than that of spike-and slow-wave complexes repeating at slower rates. Comment: this pattern should be distinguished from epileptiform discharges. Synonym: wave and spike phantom." ;
    heda:inLibrary "score" ;
    heda:suggestedTag hedt:Appearance-mode,
        hedt:Brain-laterality,
        hedt:Brain-region,
        hedt:Discharge-pattern,
        hedt:Sensors ;
    hed:hasHedParent hedt:Uncertain-significant-pattern .

